cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.CG, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with generating visual contours and a simplified visual-surface planar map for stylized vector art illustration of a mesh. This involves adapting an energy minimizing active contour method designed for robust mesh processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GR (Computer Graphics), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry). The paper also mentions tracking contours as the mesh animates, which suggests a possible connection to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
